The paper proposes a novel hierarchical control mechanism for bipedal locomotion using artificial central pattern generators (CPGs) and neural networks. This topic falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO) as it involves controlling a robot's movements. The use of artificial neural networks (ANNs) also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the CPG network, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of a high-level controller for modulating the CPG network suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses simulation experiments to demonstrate the feasibility of the proposed controller, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
